    {
      "id": "ee8c4785711099919a0f6f633f068ddb68489ac7",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 117,
        "name": "Andreas Dilger",
        "email": "adilger@thelustrecollective.com",
        "username": "adilger"
      },
      "date": "2022-11-11 02:13:37.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1: Code-Review-1\n\nNone of these parallel configure tests have landed to master because of issues in Oleg's test environment.  As much as I think everyone would benefit from these patches, I think porting them to b2_15 is premature, and the RHEL9 kernel series should not be based on them or it will block the landing of the RHEL9 patches.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
    {
      "id": "e7d9946db9addbfadbe0dc001150e173d482ff1a",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 808,
        "name": "Shaun Tancheff",
        "email": "shaun.tancheff@hpe.com",
        "username": "stancheff"
      },
      "date": "2022-11-11 06:08:00.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\n> Patch Set 1: Code-Review-1\n> \n> None of these parallel configure tests have landed to master because of issues in Oleg's test environment.  As much as I think everyone would benefit from these patches, I think porting them to b2_15 is premature, and the RHEL9 kernel series should not be based on them or it will block the landing of the RHEL9 patches.\n\nAll the parallel series should be passing Oleg's environment now.\n\nIn the meantime I will convert all the stacked series back to serial for now.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    }
  ],
